
[1]life-blood

   LI'FE-BLOOD, n.

   1. The blood necessary to life; vital blood.

   2. That which constitutes or gives strength and energy.

   Money, the life-blood of the nation.

           LI'FE-BLOOD, a. Necessary as blood to life; essential.
